-- U.S. Bond Mutual Funds Received Net Redemptions of $4.4 Billion Last Week
-- B y   C h a r l e s   S t e i n
-- 2010-12-29T22:30:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-29/u-s-bond-mutual-funds-received-net-redemptions-of-4-4-billion-last-week.html
U.S. bond mutual funds had net
redemptions of $4.4 billion last week, with $837 million
withdrawals from taxable bond funds and $3.5 billion from
municipal bond funds, an industry report showed.  Stock mutual funds in the U.S. attracted a net $3.9 billion
in the week ending Dec. 21, according to an e-mailed statement
today from the Investment Company Institute, a Washington-based
trade group.  To contact the reporter on this story:
